   9. THE HUNDRED DAYS, by Patrick O'Brian. (Norton, $24.)
</P>
<P>
   In 1815, Jack Aubrey and Stephen Maturin must intercept
</P>
<P>
   a shipment of gold intended to aid Napoleon.
</P>
<P>
   10. THE REEF, by Nora Roberts. (Putnam, $23.95.)
</P>
<P>
   Searching for a jeweled amulet in the depths of
</P>
<P>
   the Caribbean, a woman deals with mysteries and romance.
</P>
<P>
   11. MEMOIRS OF A GEISHA, by Arthur Golden. (Knopf, $25.)
</P>
<P>
   The life of a young woman growing up in Kyoto who has
</P>
<P>
   to reinvent herself after World War II begins.
</P>
<P>
   12. THE HAMMER OF EDEN, by Ken Follett. (Crown, $25.95.)
</P>
<P>
   An FBI agent finds herself on the trail of terrorists
</P>
<P>
   planning a man-made earthquake in California.
</P>
<P>
   13. TODAY I FEEL SILLY &AMP; OTHER MOODS THAT MAKE MY DAY,
</P>
<P>
   by Jamie Lee Curtis. Illustrated by Laura Cornell.
</P>
<P>
   (Cotter/HarperCollins, $15.95.) The ever-changing
</P>
<P>
   moods of a young girl.
</P>
<P>
   14.(x) THE LOCKET, by Richard Paul Evans. (Simon &AMP; Schuster,
</P>
<P>
   $15.95.) A young man learns much about life, love and compassion
</P>
<P>
   while working in a nursing home.
</P>
<P>
   15. I KNOW THIS MUCH IS TRUE, by Wally Lamb.
</P>
<P>
   (Regan Books/HarperCollins, $27.50.) A troubled
</P>
<P>
   man must care for his schizophrenic identical
</P>
<P>
   twin brother and face the nightmares that have
</P>
<P>
   bedeviled their family.
</P>
