<HEADLINE>
`GODZILLA' A DULL LIZARD;   `WILD MAN BLUES' REVEALING 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES:  &UR; ``Godzilla''  &LR; _ The lead-footed remake of the
cheesy Japanese original features superior technology and little
else. Humorless and dull. The performances are as mechanical as the
monster. The only redeeming quality is that the failure of
``Godzilla'' to generate profits on the big screen temporarily
might slow down Hollywood's rush to remake high-tech trash.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``Wild Man Blues'' &LR;  _ I always thought Woody Allen, in spite of
his so-called personal life choices, was a pretty smart guy. But,
after watching Barbara Kopple's nonfiction account of Allen's jazz
band's European tour, you start to wonder. While Allen the film
director is a control freak, in his private life he's humiliated in
one excruciating sequence by his mother. Allen is seen as a grown
man desperately seeking the approval of his distant mother. No
wonder his episode of ``New York Stories'' was titled ``Oedipus
Wrecks.'' His wife, Soon Yi Previn, seems to take particular
delight in stating she's never seen ``Annie Hall.'' No wonder he's
got the blues.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   DIRECT TO VIDEO: ``The Lion King 2: Simba's Pride'' isn't the
only feature-length animated film to get the home video sequel
treatment. ``The Land Before Time,'' the successful dinosaur
cartoon, has spawned five sequels. The latest, ``The Land Before
Time VI: Secret of Saurus Rock'' is due in stores Dec. 1. ``The
Secret of Nimh 2: Timmy to the Rescue,'' returns to Thorn Valley
and into video outlets on Dec. 22.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS:  &UR; Nov. 10:  &LR; ``Artemesia,'' ``The Horse
Whisperer,'' ``Small Soldiers,'' ``For Richer or Poorer,'' ``The
Landlady,'' ``James Ellroy: Demon Dog of American Crime Fiction,''
``Tracked,'' ``Tales of the Tooth Fairy.''  &UR; Nov. 13:
 &LR; ``Armageddon.''  &UR; Nov. 17:  &LR; ``Fear and Loathing in Las Vegas,''
``An All Dogs Christmas Carol,'' ``Photographing Fairies,'' ``Dirty
Work,'' ``The Land Girls,'' ``Can't Hardly Wait,'' ``High Art,''
``My Husband's Secret Life,'' ``Passion in the Desert,'' ``Music
from Another Room.''  &UR; Nov. 24:  &LR; ``Dr. Dolittle,'' ``Soldier of
Fortune,'' ``Phoenix,'' ``Sliding Doors.''  &UR; Dec. 1:  &LR; ``The Mask of
Zorro.''  &UR; Dec. 8:  &LR; ``The Parent Trap,'' ``Lured,'' ``Double Edge,''
``It Happened Tomorrow.''  &UR; Dec. 15: &LR;  ``The Boxer,'' ``Madeline,''
``Half Baked.''  &UR; Dec. 22:  &LR; ``Blade,'' ``Baseketball,'' ``Billy's
Hollywood Screen Kiss.''
</P>
</TEXT>
