<BODY>
 AM-ADD-NYT-BUDGET  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Add N.Y. Times News Service budget for papers of TUESDAY, Nov.
3.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SCIENCE/HEALTH&AMP;FITNESS  &LR; (Coded ``a'')
</P>
<P>
   SCI-PATRICK-TERROR-PROFILE (Frederick, Md.) _ Scientist at Work:
The United States is fast becoming better prepared to defend itself
against the menace of biological terrorism, largely through the
efforts of Bill Patrick, now 72. By William F. Broad and Judith
Miller. With photo and graphic.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-SLEEP-DEPRIVATION (Undated) _ Depending on what the FDA
decides to do next month, the sleep deprivation problems of the
country may be alleviated. Late last year, the FDA added to its
approvable drug list a new compound called modafinil. By Dec. 31,
the agency is scheduled to decide whether the drug can be marketed
for narcolepsy, a severe sleep disorder that afflicts about one in
100 Americans. If approved, it could help scientists unlock some of
the remaining mysteries of sleep and waking. By Erica Goode.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-CONDUCTOR (Undated) _ After 87 years, during which exuberant
hopes have alternated with disappointments, the world's first
superconducting power line _ a line that will conduct huge
electrical currents with far less resistance than that of a line
made of metal wire _ is to become a reality in mid-2000 in Detroit.
By Malcolm W. Browne. With graphic.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-SHUTTLE (Cape Canaveral) _ The Discovery crew is conducting
one of the most ambitious and diverse programs of scientific and
commercial research yet attempted on a nine-day mission. By Warren
E. Leary. With graphic.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-MOM-ESSAY (Undated) _ When children are born with birth
defects, well-meaning doctors often quiz parents, especially
mothers, about their habits, medications, family history, and so
on. This conveys to parents an inadvertent message of blame. And
mothers are most likely to feel responsible for everything. By
Alice Dreger.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-ZOO-NATURE (Undated) _ Sometime in mid-December, Timmy and
Dan, two silverback male gorillas, and their respective troops will
move into new quarters at the Bronx Zoo, in an environment designed
by scientists and animal experts to resemble a central African rain
forest, the animals' natural habitat. With photo. By Shelly
Freierman.
</P>
<P>
   HEALTH-EYE-LASER (Undated) _ Authorities now expect laser
surgery to be available for the farsighted next year, adding to the
more than 400,000 who annually have the procedure for
nearsightedness. The proposal is before the FDA. Photo and Graphic.
By Anne Eisenberg. With photo and graphic.
</P>
<P>
   BRODY-HEALTH (Undated) _ Personal Health: Depression among older
people is an often unrecognized and untreated problem that can
tarnish the golden years for millions of Americans. By Jane E.
Brody. With graphic. (coded ``l'')
</P>
<P>
   HEALTH-PRIVACY (Undated) _ Medical privacy as we once understood
