<P>
   UNDATED _ Neither death nor grief is a stranger to me. And
neither are the words and experiences shared in the
soon-to-be-released ``A Broken Heart Still Beats: After Your Child
Dies,'' (Hazelden) a compilation of excerpts from poems, works of
fiction and essays that articulate the chaos of feelings that comes
with such a loss. By GRACIE BONDS STAPLES. Story has moved in ``l''
lifestyle category. (Accompanied by GRIEF-EXCERPTS.) &QL; 
 &QL; 
