<P>
   UNDATED _ ``Freedom is like an insurance policy,'' Sam Rayburn
used to say. ``Its premiums have to kept up to date.'' Voting is
our way of doing that. It's a right won by heroes' blood, and a
duty no less imperative to the survival of a free society than
bearing arms in its defense. By JIM WRIGHT. Story has moved in
``k'' commentary category. &QL; 
