   BUSINESS/FINANCIAL NEWS (``f'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BMC-BOOLE-MERGER (Houston) _ BMC Software of Houston and Boole &AMP;
Babbage of San Francisco had been talking for two months about a
potential merger, but their customers already had been putting the
two companies together. The executives behind the $900-million
acquisition say their users had been integrating their products for
years. By DWIGHT SILVERMAN.
</P>
<P>
   PIRACY-SOFTWARE (Houston) _ Software giant Microsoft Corp. says
it has filed lawsuits against seven Texas companies, alleging
infringement of Microsoft copyrights and trademarks. By DWIGHT
SILVERMAN.
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ Does the blockbuster revelation that
President Thomas Jefferson fathered at least one child with slave
Sally Hemings undercut his reputation as one of our greatest and
most brilliant leaders? Does the timing of this news help fellow
philanderer President Clinton? The answer to both questions is no.
By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
