<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Kansas City Star plans to move the following stories for use
by clients of the NYTimes News Service for AMs and PMs of Tuesday,
Nov. 3. If you have any questions, please call the Star's News Desk
at (816) 234-4720.
CHILEANS-REMEMBER _ (KANSAS CITY, MO.) _ Marco Cruz and Luis
Ramirez shared a dream. Both men _ one a construction worker, the
other an educator _ wanted social justice for Chile.
</P>
<P>
   They shared a nightmare, too.
</P>
<P>
   Both were tortured in the 1970s for opposing the dictatorship of
Augusto Pinochet. By OSCAR AVILA. Two takes. Story will move in
``a'' category.
TRUMAN-UPSET _ (KANSAS CITY, Mo.) _ Harry Truman needed a
diversion.
</P>
<P>
   On Nov. 2, 1948 _ Election Day _ he waited in his Independence
home while a motorcycle roared out of his driveway, heading west on
Van Horn Road to Kansas City.
</P>
<P>
   A car followed. By BRIAN BURNES. Two takes. Story will move in
``a'' category.
</P>
</TEXT>
