<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Morissette's `Junkie' hits stores today
 &HT;    By Russ Devault
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Just call them dueling divas: Pop stars Celine Dion and Alanis
Morissette release new albums today, and it's a given that Dion's
seasonal collection, ``These Are Special Times,'' and Morissette's
``Supposed Former Infatuation Junkie'' will be huge sellers
throughout the holidays.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think Alanis will do the most Tuesday, but Celine's
Christmas album will do well in time,'' says Calvin Thorbourne, a
manager at Buckhead's HMV Music. Other releases expected to attract
buyers today, Thorbourne adds, include Oasis' B-sides collection,
``The Masterplan,'' and the ``Belly'' urban-music soundtrack.
</P>
<P>
   Fans should note that Dion, who has sold more than 60 million
albums worldwide during the past 30 months, will star in her first
TV special, ``These Are Special Times,'' for CBS on Nov. 25.
</P>
<P>
   Also new in stores
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Belly'' soundtrack (Def Jam/PolyGram). Includes tracks by
DMX, Method Man, Tionne ``T-Boz'' Watkins of TLC.
</P>
<P>
   -- Billy Ray Cyrus, ``Shot Full of Love'' (Mercury).
</P>
<P>
   -- Celine Dion, ``These Are Special Times'' (550 Music/Sony).
Grade: C.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``The John Lennon Anthology'' (Capitol). Tower, other
retailers selling four-CD box for about $60.
</P>
<P>
   -- Alanis Morissette, ``Supposed Former Infatuation Junkie''
(Maverick/Warner Bros.). Review in Thursday's Living. Grade: B.
</P>
<P>
   -- Oasis, ``The Masterplan'' (Epic).
</P>
<P>
   -- Marcus Roberts, ``The Joy of Joplin'' (Sony Classical).
</P>
<P>
   -- The Rolling Stones, ``No Security'' (Virgin).
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Touched by an Angel _ The Soundtrack'' (550 Music/Sony).
Artists include Celine Dion, Bob Dylan, Deana Carter.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
