 &HT;    Sampras reminds tennis world of record year
 &HT;    By Todd Holcomb
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Pete Sampras isn't one to seek out attention, but he made a good
point last week when he noted that his pursuit of a record
sixth-straight year finishing No. 1 on the ATP Tour computer is
getting surprisingly little attention worldwide.
</P>
<P>
   It escaped almost everyone's notice last year when Sampras tied
Jimmy Connors' record of five in a row.
</P>
<P>
   ``Even in Europe, it wasn't really talked about,'' said Sampras,
who is still ranked No. 1 but stands second in points this year
behind Marcelo Rios with just three weeks remaining.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's disappointing because it's one of the toughest things to
do in sports,'' Sampras said. ``There is no doubt about how hard it
is to stay on top in any sport, but to do it in an individual sport
for the majority of his career, it's not easy.''
</P>
<P>
   It might be comparing apples to orang
</P>
