<P>
   BOEING-TOOL (Seattle) _ In an embarassing quality control
incident for The Boeing Co. that is akin to a surgeon leaving an
operating room instrument inside a patient, a manufacturing tool
was left inside the rudder of a new 767 widebody jet. The tool,
known as ``bucking bar'' and used by riveters, bounced and banged
around inside the rudder for two years before it was recently
discovered during maintenance.
</P>
<P>
   By James Wallace. (Story will move in the ``f'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   ARTHRITIS-DRUG _ A genetically engineered drug developed by a
Seattle company won government approval Monday to help some of the
hardest-to-treat sufferers of rheumatoid arthritis. Immunex Corp.'s
Enbrel can fight debilitating symptoms in advanced rheumatoid
arthritis patients _ and appears to cause fewer serious side
effects than older therapies.
</P>
<P>
   By Carol Smith. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
