11-2 -- Telegraph Avenue, the main business street of Berkeley, is
a haven for youths and the homeless, but not for much longer if the
city has its way. Whether they are scared or just plain fed up,
plenty of people in the nation's most famously liberal city want
the youths, panhandlers, drug addicts, drinkers, mentally ill
homeless swept off Telegraph Avenue, the shopping district here
mentioned in every tourist guide. (Audrey Shehyn/New York Times
Photo)
