<P>
   (NYT2) BOSTON -- Nov. 2, 1998 -- MUSIC-DOCTOR-BOS, 11-2 -- Dr.
Michael Charness works with flutist Marie Fukuda, at Boston's
Brigham &AMP; Women's Hospital. Charness, director of Brigham and
Women's ``performing arts clinic,'' is one of a handful of doctors
that specializes in physical ailments plaguing professional
musicians. (Tom Herde/Boston Globe Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT1) PURCHASE, N.Y. -- Nov. 02, 1998 -- BKN-MARCUS-CANBY,
11-01 -- Marcus Canby, 24, stands behind his closet friend, Tamia
Murray, 23, on the patio of the house he is renting. Murray is a
former hustler who sold drugs, mixed in a seamy nightclub scene and
pulled countless scams, played a prominent role in an agent scandal
that left Canby's school, the University of Connecticut, stripped
of its 1996 Final Four appearance and Canby's name disgraced.
(Joyce Dopkeen/New York Times Photo)
