<HEADLINE>
TROJANS BEEF UP DEFENSE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ USC's defensive line has been further bolstered as
Sagan Atuatasi, a 6-foot-2, 285-pound tackle from Los Alamitos has
orally committed to the Trojans.
</P>
<P>
   Atuatasi is a teammate of Bernard Riley, who committed to USC
earlier this month. Atuatasi is listed as the 19th-best defensive
lineman in the country, according to SuperPrep magazine.
</P>
<P>
   Atuatasi also considered UCLA, Washington and Colorado. He is
the third defensive lineman to commit to USC, which has benefited
early from the recruiting skills of defensive line coach Ed
Orgeron.
</P>
<P>
   The Trojans also have a commitment from defensive tackle Malcolm
Woolridge (6-2, 300) of Boca Raton, Fla. Six players have committed
to USC this year.
</P>
<P>
   __ Where's Soward?: USC's offense the past two games has barely
featured wide receiver R. Jay Soward, the Trojans' most explosive
player.
</P>
<P>
   Soward caught just three passes for 9 yards against Oregon, and
only one pass for 16 yards against Washington.
</P>
<P>
   ``I would have liked to do a little more, but you can't always
have your way,'' Soward said. ``Washington was really trying to
take our speed away.''
</P>
<P>
   Soward is no longer even USC's leading receiver. He has 27
receptions, which puts him six behind Billy Miller.
</P>
<P>
   __ Bastianelli tries kicking: Wide receiver Mike Bastianelli
tried his first attempt at kicking in nearly three years during
Sunday's practice, following Adam Abrams' 0-for-2 performance
against Washington.
</P>
<P>
   Both Abrams and David Bell continued kicking in practice,
however, and it would be surprising if Bastianelli actually kicked
in a game.
</P>
<P>
   __ Simmons honored: Cornerback Antuan Simmons was named the
Pacific-10 Conference's defensive player of the week after
returning two interceptions for touchdowns against Washington. It
was the third time Simmons has been honored by the Pac-10. He was
previously named defensive player of the week for the Purdue game
and special-teams player of the week for the Arizona State game.
</P>
<P>
   __ UCLA game time set: USC's game against UCLA at the Rose Bowl
Nov. 21 will be at 12:30 p.m. and televised by ABC-TV.
</P>
<P>
   __ Power rankings: USC is not in either top-25 poll, but the
Trojans have moved from 24th to 19th in the latest New York Times
computer rankings.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
