<HEADLINE>
BROOKHART SET TO ATTEND A&AMP;M
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JEFF SULLIVAN 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Former Crowley High School basketball standout Brian Brookhart
will enroll at Texas A&AMP;M for the second semester of classes and
walk on to the men's basketball team.
</P>
<P>
   Brookhart, a 6-foot-10, 225-pound freshman, was signed by TCU
during his senior season at Crowley, but was released from his
scholarship in August by TCU coach Billy Tubbs after the coaching
staff suggested Brookhart enroll in a junior college to further
develop his game. Since then, Brookhart has been attending classes
part time at TCU under an institutional aid plan.
</P>
<P>
   ``Texas A&AMP;M is a first-rate program with first-rate coaches, and
I plan on spending the next four years there,'' Brookhart said.
``They \RA&AMP;M coaches\S said that they would give me the chance to
earn a scholarship for next season, because they had none left this
season, and that's all I asked for.''
</P>
<P>
   Brookhart said that Texas offered a scholarship beginning
immediately but that he declined. Other schools in Texas showing
interest included Lamar and UT-Pan American.
</P>
</TEXT>
